ll differentiation\nintersection_of: GO:0030154 ! cell differentiation\nintersection_of: results_in_acquisition_of_features_of CL:0002280\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30979\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-10-31T00:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770025\nname: intestinal type D enteroendocrine cell differentiation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of an intestinal type D enteroendocrine cell. Intestinal type D enteroendocrine cells are found in the gastrointestinal tract and in the pancreas and secrete somatostatin.\" [PMID:37883554]\nis_a: GO:0035883 ! enteroendocrine cell differentiation\nintersection_of: GO:0030154 ! cell differentiation\nintersection_of: results_in_acquisition_of_features_of CL:0000502 ! type D enteroendocrine cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30979\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-10-31T00:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770026\nname: N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine transmembrane transporter activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Enables the transfer of N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine from one side of a membrane to the other.\" [PMID:41075780, PMID:41075794]\nxref: RHEA:86419 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nintersection_of: GO:0022857 ! transmembrane transporter activity\nintersection_of: has_primary_input CHEBI:58100 ! N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine zwitterion\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30986\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770027\nname: dimethylarginine transmembrane transporter activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Enables the transfer of dimethylarginine from one side of a membrane to the other.\" [PMID:41075780, PMID:41075794]\nxref: RHEA:75047 {source